<|startoftext|>Dish: easy amaretto french toast
Directions: heat 1 teaspoons in 1 cup melted butter in skillet
add flour and stir until mixture is crumbly
set aside , reserving 1 cup for glaze
beat egg with milk until fluffy
gradually beat in 1 / 2 cup of the hot butter
fold in buttermilk and flour mixture
pour onto 1 half of the pan and top with remaining butter , 1 / 2 cup at a time
top with remaining butter
cook until butter melts without lifting edge of pan
brush lightly with butter-flavored glaze
garnish with remaining teaspoon
to freeze , roll or cut into individual rolls
freeze in freezer airtight container'<|endoftext|>
